x.  You will be healing a lot until you get 51-52 so you wont need much really. RM for the planes is nice generally. I think above 100 for those fights (depending on which raid and how close you get to taking spell damage) would be a good start. Get some but I wouldn't worry about it too much until you start to pull planes or you start to do the Kunark dragons.  The nice thing about thinking about resist gear at your level is that a lot of it can be achieved at lower levels and so you want to remember to keep it around for the later levels. <br>
<br>
Durga has a good amount of resist gear for druids. There is a book and  bracers good for FR and CR. Earrings for MR. Vox bracers for CR. Mammoth cloak for CR. Giants in GD have a beard for CR. Planes gear is nice for resists. CoS from Sol B is good for RD. There is a shield in Hate for FR and a shield off the dwarfs in Thurg (that people would probably let you loot) for CR. Tranix crown is nice. A veil(FR) and runed morning star (MR)in Howling Stones. Of course our epic weapon is chocked full of resists. Mask of Jarsath is good. As you get older you can look for items in Dragon Necropolis and the quest armor. WW dragons have neck pieces with all resists on them. Velks Maze has some good CR cape and minor resists in a boot.<br>
<br>
Then you go on to player made jewelry. That really depends on if you have good resists or need something special. After all my work on resists I was doing ok with CR FR and getting there with DR but my PR was bad, so when I won a blue diamond I went with earring that was mixed resists favoring PR and DR since I had no resist gear in that slot so it was a pick up of all resists. Look at the chart and see if combo jewelry offers the same resists as some of the individual resists. When you get higher and need a lot of resists carry the least amount of stuff as possible is really helpful. <br>
<br>
For the lower levels general resist gear is pretty good. But as you get up for the Kunark Dragons and VP and the ToV raids you will want to go with specific resists for those specific fights and switch around gear for the next fight specific to that mob. This is most important even at the cost of drastic amounts of AC and WIS.  We all look pretty bad too.  :) For those raids I am unbuffed over 125 resist for CR DR and FR. PR is bad at 100 and MR is at 146. With the epic weapon soonish,  I will push that to 135 CR DR FR, 110 PR and 150 MR<br>
<br>
What I think is good about this is you are thinking about this early and can spend some time working on it while maybe getting exp for it still, unlike me who started working on it more about 5am after the night I completed my key for VP and 5 hours before my first raid :)<br>
 <p>-Bern Fizzlesticks <BR>
 Imbuer of cowpies
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueyeds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyeds</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/22/01 11:19:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist Gear Question</span><hr size=1> I would buy the specific peices of jewlry, dont worry about ac or wis just get your resists up as much as you can.  If you are dead mana means nothing =( <p>Eyed
